    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="executeBulkStatusUpdate lift" location="src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx#L731">Lift the bulk update pattern into framework `BulkUpdateField` handler; EventsPage registers an Event-specific variant.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Xrm.App.sidePanes Calendar" location="src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx">Existing Calendar pane mount logic — preserve.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run `/fluent-v9-component` skill Step 0.5 checklist.</step>
    <step order="2">Audit existing App.tsx: identify what stays (Calendar pane, handler registration), what moves to framework (CRUD ops, grid, filters), what's deleted (IEventRecord, Event-specific filter components).</step>
    <step order="3">Author new `App.tsx` (~150 lines): parse URL params → register `BulkUpdateEventStatus` handler → mount `<FluentProvider applyStylesToPortals>` + `<DataGrid configId={EVENT_CONFIG_ID} dataverseClient={new XrmDataverseClient()}/>` + Calendar pane in `Xrm.App.sidePanes`.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `registerEventHandlers.ts`: exports `registerEventHandlers(registry)` that calls `registry.registerCommandHandler("BulkUpdateEventStatus", (selectedIds, args) => ...)` lifting from existing `executeBulkStatusUpdate`.</step>
    <step order="5">Preserve Calendar pane mutual exclusivity — if Event detail pane opens, Calendar collapses; vice versa.</step>
    <step order="6">Delete `IEventRecord` and any Event-typed grid components from App.tsx (they're now in framework).</step>
    <step order="7">Build (`npm run build` in `src/solutions/EventsPage/`); verify single-file HTML output.</step>
    <step order="8">Local dev test: `npm run dev`; verify mock URL renders.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify line count: `wc -l src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx` shows ≤200.</step>
    <step order="10">Grep for forbidden: `grep -E 'IEventRecord|GridSection|AssignedToFilter|RecordTypeFilter|StatusFilter' src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx` returns nothing.</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX (031 ✅).</step>
    <step order="12">Document deviations in `notes/drafts/031-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build + Vite dev</tool>
    <tool name="grep">Verify forbidden patterns removed</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Rewrite App.tsx</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx (rewritten)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/EventsPage/src/registerEventHandlers.ts</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `wc -l src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx`, when run, then result is ≤200 lines.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given grep for `IEventRecord` in App.tsx, when run, then zero matches.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given dev build, when run, then single-file HTML output produced.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given local dev mount with mock URL, when DataGrid renders, then Event rows visible with allowlist chips (4 chips).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `BulkUpdateEventStatus` handler invoked with mock selectedIds + payload, when run, then bulk Promise.all delete/update fires correctly.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="EventsPage all 4 modes (UAT in task 035)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_eventspage</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open EventsPage in system mode; verify renders</step>
        <step>Verify Calendar pane visible</step>
        <step>Click row; verify record opens (record-link bug closure check)</step>
        <step>Toggle dark mode; re-verify</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Renders identically pre/post migration; record-link works in dialog</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    The biggest refactor in the project. The line count target (≤200) is the proof point — if the host can't shrink to that, something's wrong with the framework abstraction. Calendar pane mutual exclusivity is the easiest thing to accidentally break; verify it explicitly. Don't delete the 4 retiring files yet — that's task 032 (after this lands).
  </notes>

  <execution>
